4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to authorize the
7 Legislature, by general law, to provide full
8 legislative participation on any bonding authority in
9 order to limit the issuance of bonds or incurrance of
10 other debt.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
18 of 2022, relating to bonding authorities; to authorize the
19 Legislature, by general law, to provide for legislative
20 participation on any authority that issues bonds.
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
22 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
23 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
24 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
25 The Legislature, by general law, may provide for full
26 legislative participation on any authority, board, or other
27 entity with the power to issue bonds or otherwise become
28 indebted. Legislative participation includes the power to
Page 1

indebted. Legislative participation includes the power to
